      { heading: 'What Changes Operationally Once You Have a Fixed Shop', level: 2 as const, body: 'The transition itself also becomes smoother with a system already in place. A machinga moving into a duka does not need to learn a new way of tracking sales — the same AskBiz habits carry over directly, just with a fixed location instead of a moving one. What does change is the ability to add more structure: formal stock counts, supplier relationships that require invoices, and potentially the POS add-on for handling a higher volume of transactions once foot traffic is concentrated in one place rather than spread across a walking route. Traders who already have the tracking habit built in find this upgrade far less disruptive than those trying to build both a new shop and a new record-keeping system at the same time.' }
